1
00:02:05,425 --> 00:02:07,825
Jake, honey,
it's time to get up.

2
00:02:16,035 --> 00:02:17,559
Good morning.

3
00:02:17,770 --> 00:02:19,567
Good morning, Bette.

4
00:02:23,543 --> 00:02:26,535
It's a little chilly.
I'll put out a sweater.

5
00:02:26,880 --> 00:02:27,869
Hmm-mmm.

6
00:02:42,795 --> 00:02:44,023
Get dressed now.

7
00:02:44,097 --> 00:02:45,962
I want to be there
when they open.

8
00:02:46,032 --> 00:02:47,021
Okay.

9
00:03:16,763 --> 00:03:19,425
I already put sugar in.
One is enough.

10
00:03:22,902 --> 00:03:24,631
Here's your napkin.

11
00:03:39,586 --> 00:03:41,486
You want that buttered?

12
00:03:50,230 --> 00:03:51,663
There you go.

13
00:04:50,223 --> 00:04:51,212
Good morning.

14
00:04:57,463 --> 00:05:00,091
Watch your step.
The inspector's here.

15
00:05:04,370 --> 00:05:05,894
Good morning, Mrs. Tremont.

16
00:05:05,972 --> 00:05:07,633
Good morning, Mr. Korman.

17
00:05:07,707 --> 00:05:08,731
Mr. Tremont.

18
00:05:08,808 --> 00:05:09,832
Hello.

19
00:05:09,909 --> 00:05:11,501
The Dodgers did
okay last night. Huh?

20
00:05:11,577 --> 00:05:13,067
Yes.

21
00:05:13,980 --> 00:05:16,210
What can I do for you,
Mrs. Tremont?

22
00:05:16,282 --> 00:05:18,443
It says pork chops on sale.

23
00:05:18,518 --> 00:05:21,487
Yes, indeed. Just
follow me right over here.

24
00:05:22,188 --> 00:05:24,247
All of these in
this row right here,

25
00:05:24,324 --> 00:05:26,349
on sale as advertised.

26
00:05:26,893 --> 00:05:29,293
What about
these pork chops here?

27
00:05:29,362 --> 00:05:30,852
Those are not
the ones on sale.

28
00:05:30,930 --> 00:05:33,057
The ad just says
pork chops, Mr. Korman.

29
00:05:33,132 --> 00:05:34,724
It doesn't have
their pictures

30
00:05:34,801 --> 00:05:36,996
or their ID numbers.
It just says pork chops.

31
00:05:37,070 --> 00:05:39,402
What is it that you want,
Mrs. Tremont?

32
00:05:39,472 --> 00:05:42,236
I want these pork chops
at those prices.

33
00:05:44,677 --> 00:05:46,042
You got it.

34
00:06:06,866 --> 00:06:08,060
Jake.
HUH?

35
00:06:09,335 --> 00:06:10,324
Jake.

36
00:06:13,706 --> 00:06:15,037
UH...

37
00:06:18,778 --> 00:06:20,006
Sorry to drop this
on you, John, first thing,

38
00:06:20,079 --> 00:06:22,343
but I have one personnel
problem you should know about.

39
00:06:22,415 --> 00:06:25,248
This kid we want to hire can't
decide between us and Goldman.

40
00:06:25,318 --> 00:06:26,342
I know you hate this,

41
00:06:26,419 --> 00:06:27,647
but I think you have
to step in

42
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:29,153
and use
your magic touch.

43
00:06:29,222 --> 00:06:30,780
Oh, is he really that good?

44
00:06:30,923 --> 00:06:32,515
I can't stand this
recruiting stuff.

45
00:06:32,592 --> 00:06:34,116
All these kids out
of business school

46
00:06:34,193 --> 00:06:35,626
think they're worth $100,000

47
00:06:35,695 --> 00:06:37,094
after one week on the job.

48
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:38,663
I hate their attitudes.

49
00:06:38,731 --> 00:06:40,631
You know,
when I was that age,

50
00:06:40,700 --> 00:06:42,759
I had to walk a mile
in the snow for a stock tip.

51
00:06:42,835 --> 00:06:44,462
This kid's special.
I think you'll find

52
00:06:44,537 --> 00:06:46,528
that out if you spend
a little time with him.

53
00:06:46,606 --> 00:06:49,040
All right, arrange it with Kathy
for sometime later this week.

54
00:06:49,108 --> 00:06:50,700
I'm booked
for the next few days.

55
00:06:50,777 --> 00:06:52,711
Well, the Vale prospectus
is shaping up well

56
00:06:52,779 --> 00:06:54,940
but management is resisting
our suggestions

57
00:06:55,014 --> 00:06:57,380
that we provide data
to help investors understand

58
00:06:57,450 --> 00:06:59,247
why the company
is so profitable.

59
00:06:59,318 --> 00:07:02,446
They're afraid of giving too much
information to their competitors.

60
00:07:02,522 --> 00:07:03,511
I don't know

61
00:07:03,589 --> 00:07:05,523
why we're dealing
with this Vale guy anyway.

62
00:07:05,591 --> 00:07:06,615
He's a shady character.

63
00:07:06,692 --> 00:07:08,922
I think we're risking
the reputation of the firm.

64
00:07:08,995 --> 00:07:11,486
If we turn him down, we'll
never get his business again.

65
00:07:11,564 --> 00:07:12,997
There's a huge fee involved

66
00:07:13,065 --> 00:07:14,999
and the banking division
needs the business.

67
00:07:15,067 --> 00:07:16,967
I'm worrying
about my bonus this year.

68
00:07:17,036 --> 00:07:18,196
Oh, mark that down.

69
00:07:18,271 --> 00:07:21,331
I think that's the earliest
worrying about a bonus ever recorded.

70
00:07:23,075 --> 00:07:24,201
Yeah?

71
00:07:24,377 --> 00:07:26,675
It's your sister, Mr. Tremont.

72
00:07:26,813 --> 00:07:29,907
She says it's important.
She's has to talk to you now.

73
00:07:30,183 --> 00:07:31,514
Hi, Annie. How are you?

74
00:07:31,584 --> 00:07:32,881
I'm in a meeting. What's up?

75
00:07:32,952 --> 00:07:34,476
John, it's about Mom.

76
00:07:34,554 --> 00:07:36,044
She's had a heart attack.

77
00:07:36,122 --> 00:07:38,682
She's okay,
but it's pretty serious.

78
00:07:38,758 --> 00:07:40,225
Can you come out?

79
00:07:50,336 --> 00:07:51,325
Hey!

80
00:07:51,437 --> 00:07:52,426
How was your flight?

81
00:07:52,505 --> 00:07:53,529
All right.

82
00:07:53,606 --> 00:07:55,574
The guy next to me
wouldn't leave me alone.

83
00:07:55,641 --> 00:07:57,666
Once they hear you're on
Wall Street, forget it.

84
00:07:57,743 --> 00:08:00,473
"What about this stock? What about
that stock? What about bonds?"

85
00:08:00,546 --> 00:08:01,570
Yeah, I know.

86
00:08:01,647 --> 00:08:03,274
Ever heard of
a stock called Chrometex?

87
00:08:03,349 --> 00:08:04,338
Mario.

88
00:08:04,417 --> 00:08:06,408
A guy in the math department
told me about it.

89
00:08:06,486 --> 00:08:08,579
They make those heat sensors
for cryogenic capsules.

90
00:08:08,654 --> 00:08:10,315
It's gonna be bigger
than the telephone.

91
00:08:10,389 --> 00:08:11,651
No, it's not.

92
00:08:11,724 --> 00:08:12,691
It's not?

93
00:08:12,758 --> 00:08:13,850
No.

94
00:08:18,731 --> 00:08:20,289
How's Annie?
How's she holding up?

95
00:08:20,366 --> 00:08:21,924
Good. She's at home
with your father.

96
00:08:22,001 --> 00:08:23,593
We can go there first
or the hospital.

97
00:08:23,669 --> 00:08:24,658
Whatever.

98
00:08:24,737 --> 00:08:26,204
Let's go to the hospital.

99
00:08:26,339 --> 00:08:27,806
That's what I figured.

100
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:29,337
How's Dad?

101
00:08:29,408 --> 00:08:31,569
To be honest, Johnny,
he's a little shook up.

102
00:08:31,644 --> 00:08:32,941
That's why Annie's there.

103
00:08:33,012 --> 00:08:34,639
She didn't want
to leave him alone.

104
00:08:35,748 --> 00:08:37,147
So what's going on with Mom?

105
00:08:37,283 --> 00:08:38,682
How serious is this?

106
00:08:38,751 --> 00:08:40,776
Hard to tell with her.
You know your mother.

107
00:08:40,920 --> 00:08:42,945
She won't admit she's
actually had a heart attack.

108
00:08:43,022 --> 00:08:44,887
She's lying there
going into cardiac arrest,

109
00:08:44,957 --> 00:08:46,686
she's claiming
it's indigestion.

110
00:08:46,759 --> 00:08:47,851
She's blaming me.

111
00:08:47,927 --> 00:08:48,985
What do you mean?

112
00:08:49,061 --> 00:08:51,120
She said it was the sausages
I made for dinner.

113
00:08:51,264 --> 00:08:53,357
She claims
I was trying to kill her.

114
00:08:53,432 --> 00:08:54,694
Are you?

115
00:08:57,003 --> 00:08:59,904
No jury would convict me,
John. Believe me.

116
00:09:01,073 --> 00:09:02,597
I believe you.

117
00:09:04,143 --> 00:09:06,805
I must really be sick
if you're here.

118
00:09:06,879 --> 00:09:09,313
See, Mom,
that's why you're the best.

119
00:09:09,382 --> 00:09:11,282
Not many people
would have gone for guilt

120
00:09:11,350 --> 00:09:13,181
in your situation.

121
00:09:13,252 --> 00:09:15,846
How you feeling?
Are you in any pain?

122
00:09:16,155 --> 00:09:17,679
I'm staying alive
by willpower.

123
00:09:17,823 --> 00:09:19,347
She'll tell you.

124
00:09:20,259 --> 00:09:23,319
I've the willpower of
a woman half my age.

125
00:09:23,396 --> 00:09:25,523
You underestimate yourself.

126
00:09:25,998 --> 00:09:27,829
Did you see your father yet?

127
00:09:27,900 --> 00:09:29,697
No, I came straight
from the airport.

128
00:09:29,769 --> 00:09:31,930
When you see him,
don't say anything to him

129
00:09:32,004 --> 00:09:34,029
about the heart attack.

130
00:09:34,707 --> 00:09:38,370
Just tell him that something
went wrong with my insides.

131
00:09:39,378 --> 00:09:40,538
Okay?

132
00:09:40,913 --> 00:09:42,039
Mom.

133
00:09:42,181 --> 00:09:43,307
Listen to me.

134
00:09:44,016 --> 00:09:46,712
Just tell him it's something
with my insides.

135
00:09:46,786 --> 00:09:48,617
He'll understand that

136
00:09:48,754 --> 00:09:50,483
because I had
the hysterectomy.

137
00:09:51,958 --> 00:09:53,084
Okay.

138
00:09:54,594 --> 00:09:57,290
There's food in the freezer.
It's all marked.

139
00:09:57,363 --> 00:09:59,126
If you have to go out,

140
00:09:59,465 --> 00:10:00,864
go to McDonald's or Wendy's.

141
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:02,399
Someplace simple.

142
00:10:02,902 --> 00:10:05,234
Mom, I don't think you should
worry about Dad now.

143
00:10:05,304 --> 00:10:07,499
I think you should be
worrying about yourself.

144
00:10:07,573 --> 00:10:09,302
You had a heart attack.

145
00:10:09,375 --> 00:10:11,536
I'm not so sure
I had a heart attack.

146
00:10:11,677 --> 00:10:13,872
It felt more like
gas pains to me.

147
00:10:14,080 --> 00:10:16,275
Mom, for gas pains
they give you Tums.

148
00:10:16,349 --> 00:10:17,680
They don't hook you up

149
00:10:17,750 --> 00:10:19,513
to $20 million
worth of machines.

150
00:10:19,585 --> 00:10:22,110
Did you see the doctor
who was taking care of me?

151
00:10:22,188 --> 00:10:24,816
Because I don't think
he was a real doctor.

152
00:10:24,890 --> 00:10:27,085
He was wearing tight pants

153
00:10:27,159 --> 00:10:29,093
with a big silver
belt buckle.

154
00:10:29,462 --> 00:10:32,397
He can't be more
than 30 years old.

155
00:10:32,598 --> 00:10:34,498
They'll let anyone
through medical school

156
00:10:34,567 --> 00:10:35,591
these days.

157
00:10:50,950 --> 00:10:51,939
John!

158
00:10:57,657 --> 00:10:59,454
God, it's good to see you.

159
00:11:00,493 --> 00:11:01,983
You stopped
and saw Mom first, huh?

160
00:11:02,061 --> 00:11:03,119
Yeah.

161
00:11:03,195 --> 00:11:04,856
How did she look
to you, John, really?

162
00:11:04,930 --> 00:11:06,056
Like Mom.

163
00:11:06,132 --> 00:11:07,656
Like she was gonna
walk out of there

164
00:11:07,733 --> 00:11:08,961
dragging IV bottles with her.

165
00:11:09,035 --> 00:11:10,468
Well, it was only gas pains.

166
00:11:10,536 --> 00:11:12,003
I'm sure she told you.
Yeah.

167
00:11:12,071 --> 00:11:13,163
And the willpower?

168
00:11:13,305 --> 00:11:14,431
A woman half her age.

169
00:11:14,507 --> 00:11:16,304
So you're up to date.

170
00:11:18,010 --> 00:11:19,944
It was scary, John.
I mean it,

171
00:11:20,079 --> 00:11:22,013
I thought we
were gonna lose her.

172
00:11:22,648 --> 00:11:24,275
Where would you
like your bags, sir?

173
00:11:24,350 --> 00:11:25,647
Uh, just put them right there.

174
00:11:25,718 --> 00:11:26,707
Thank you very much.

175
00:11:26,786 --> 00:11:27,980
No luggage in
the living room.

176
00:11:28,054 --> 00:11:29,112
You know the rules.

177
00:11:29,188 --> 00:11:30,712
I'll put them in
your old bedroom.

178
00:11:30,790 --> 00:11:33,315
The living room
is still off limits?

179
00:11:33,659 --> 00:11:35,889
Look at this.
Nothing changes.

180
00:11:36,195 --> 00:11:37,219
You're kidding.

181
00:11:37,296 --> 00:11:39,787
This place is going directly
as is to the Smithsonian.

182
00:11:39,865 --> 00:11:41,025
Dad's out back, huh?

183
00:11:41,100 --> 00:11:43,068
Yeah, in the greenhouse.

184
00:11:43,569 --> 00:11:44,695
How's he doing?

185
00:11:44,770 --> 00:11:46,294
Mario said
he took it pretty hard.

186
00:11:46,372 --> 00:11:47,430
He's scared, John.

187
00:11:47,506 --> 00:11:49,201
He's really,
really frightened.

188
00:11:49,942 --> 00:11:53,002
I'm not sure he even
understands what happened.

189
00:11:53,279 --> 00:11:54,405
What do you mean?

190
00:11:54,547 --> 00:11:55,707
He's seen her, hasn't he?

191
00:11:55,781 --> 00:11:57,009
No. He was too scared.

192
00:11:57,083 --> 00:11:58,243
I didn't want to push it.

193
00:11:58,317 --> 00:12:00,308
I told him that she wasn't
allowed to have visitors,

194
00:12:00,386 --> 00:12:02,320
and he seemed okay
with that.

195
00:12:11,263 --> 00:12:12,628
Hello, Dad.

196
00:12:17,203 --> 00:12:18,693
Hello, John.

197
00:12:20,706 --> 00:12:23,197
Nice to see you.
You look good.

198
00:12:24,143 --> 00:12:25,974
Good to see you, too.

199
00:12:26,879 --> 00:12:28,904
I'm gonna be
staying here a few days.

200
00:12:28,981 --> 00:12:30,881
I know. Annie told me.

201
00:12:32,985 --> 00:12:35,010
You heard
what happened to Mother?

202
00:12:35,087 --> 00:12:38,454
Yeah. I was just at
the hospital. I saw her.

203
00:12:38,991 --> 00:12:39,980
How is she?

204
00:12:40,126 --> 00:12:41,115
Good.
Good.

205
00:12:41,193 --> 00:12:42,626
She said to say hello

206
00:12:42,695 --> 00:12:44,890
and tell you
she was comin' home soon.

207
00:12:45,231 --> 00:12:48,064
Something went wrong
with her insides, huh?

208
00:12:48,601 --> 00:12:50,933
Yeah, Dad.
Something like that.

209
00:13:03,282 --> 00:13:07,378
The heat in your
old room doesn't work,

210
00:13:07,453 --> 00:13:08,442
you know.

211
00:13:08,721 --> 00:13:11,053
You may need
an extra blanket.

212
00:13:12,391 --> 00:13:13,483
Okay.

213
00:13:16,796 --> 00:13:18,957
The main thing
for you while you're here

214
00:13:19,098 --> 00:13:21,293
will be to keep
everything on an even keel.

215
00:13:21,367 --> 00:13:22,994
Mom has a schedule

216
00:13:23,068 --> 00:13:25,628
and their life is
essentially one long routine.

217
00:13:25,704 --> 00:13:28,332
Dad gets coffee in
the morning. Decaf.

218
00:13:29,208 --> 00:13:30,869
And a sweet roll.

219
00:13:30,943 --> 00:13:34,037
They start the day by clipping
coupons, making out a shopping list.

220
00:13:34,113 --> 00:13:35,102
That's very important.

221
00:13:35,181 --> 00:13:36,648
I have a list of pills
for you here.

222
00:13:36,715 --> 00:13:38,910
When did he get so bad?
I saw him a year ago.

223
00:13:38,984 --> 00:13:40,144
No, you didn't.

224
00:13:40,219 --> 00:13:42,744
What're taking about?
I was here for Christmas.

225
00:13:42,822 --> 00:13:45,120
Annie,
I think I ought to know.

226
00:13:45,524 --> 00:13:47,617
All right,
I saw him two years ago.

227
00:13:47,693 --> 00:13:49,251
A lot happens in two years.

228
00:13:49,328 --> 00:13:50,386
Why didn't you tell me?

229
00:13:50,462 --> 00:13:52,760
I told you.
You didn't hear me.

230
00:13:54,533 --> 00:13:55,932
We tried moving
him to our place

231
00:13:56,001 --> 00:13:57,366
but he wasn't comfortable.

232
00:13:57,436 --> 00:14:00,098
It's an hour away, and we're
both working during the day.

233
00:14:00,172 --> 00:14:01,298
At least here

234
00:14:01,373 --> 00:14:02,897
he has his garden
and his greenhouse.

235
00:14:02,975 --> 00:14:04,499
He knows the environment.

236
00:14:04,577 --> 00:14:05,805
I can only stay a few days.

237
00:14:05,945 --> 00:14:07,207
What do we do after that?

238
00:14:07,279 --> 00:14:08,473
You can't stay longer?

239
00:14:08,547 --> 00:14:10,242
No. I have a meeting
in Toronto, Tuesday.

240
00:14:10,316 --> 00:14:11,806
I may have to go to Boston.

241
00:14:11,884 --> 00:14:12,976
It's just not possible.

242
00:14:13,052 --> 00:14:14,849
We're just gonna have
to bring someone in.

243
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:17,912
At least we have the time
to find the right person.

244
00:14:21,160 --> 00:14:23,094
Dad just got old, John.

245
00:14:24,163 --> 00:14:25,152
Yeah.

246
00:14:40,012 --> 00:14:42,810
Well, Dad, maybe we ought
to hit the sack, huh?

247
00:15:01,267 --> 00:15:02,256
Johnny.

248
00:15:03,969 --> 00:15:05,834
I can't find my pajamas.

249
00:15:05,971 --> 00:15:07,836
I don't know where
Mother keeps them.

250
00:15:32,298 --> 00:15:33,697
Here you go.

251
00:15:43,575 --> 00:15:45,907
Why don't you
put them on, Dad?

252
00:15:58,457 --> 00:15:59,822
I'll do it.

253
00:16:21,747 --> 00:16:23,044
You okay?

254
00:16:25,451 --> 00:16:26,941
I miss your mother.

255
00:16:31,457 --> 00:16:32,924
Well, she's getting
what she needs.

256
00:16:33,058 --> 00:16:34,548
A good rest.

257
00:16:36,929 --> 00:16:38,726
She'll be home soon.

258
00:16:42,401 --> 00:16:43,766
Good night.

259
00:16:44,403 --> 00:16:45,392
Good night.

260
00:16:46,538 --> 00:16:47,698
Leave the hall light on.

261
00:16:47,773 --> 00:16:48,899
I will.

262
00:16:48,974 --> 00:16:50,441
Sleep well.

263
00:18:30,375 --> 00:18:33,310
I don't usually eat that much
in the morning, Johnny.

264
00:18:33,378 --> 00:18:34,675
It was good, though.

